
[{"content":"","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/about/","section":"About Me","summary":"","title":"About Me","type":"about"},{"content":"44 Docker Compose stacks covering the full self-hosted stack — from reverse proxies and identity providers to monitoring, backups, and media. Click any stack to open the folder directly on GitHub.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/resources/tutorials/docker-compose/","section":"Resources","summary":"","title":"Docker Compose Stacks","type":"repo"},{"content":"My homelab is documented and version-controlled end to end. Everything from Proxmox setup to Ansible automation lives here so I can rebuild, share, or reference it at any time.\nBrowse the folders below to jump directly into any area of the setup.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/resources/homelab/","section":"Resources","summary":"","title":"homelab","type":"repo"},{"content":"A curated set of Linux configuration files built around one principle: explicit over clever. No automated installers — clone it, read it, and copy what makes sense for your setup.\nHow to Use # Clone the repo Browse the files — don\u0026rsquo;t copy blindly Symlink or copy the configs you want into your home directory (uses GNU Stow) Who It\u0026rsquo;s For # Linux power users, systems engineers, and homelab nerds who value understanding their tools. If you want a one-click install script, this isn\u0026rsquo;t it. If you want configs you can actually read and modify, start here.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/resources/linux_dotfiles/","section":"Resources","summary":"","title":"linux_dotfiles","type":"repo"},{"content":"Below are my GitHub repositories. You can click any repository to go to GitHub.\nThe list is generated by scripts/fetch_github_repos.py (run it locally, or run in CI to regenerate before deploy).\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/resources/","section":"Resources","summary":"","title":"Resources","type":"resources"},{"content":"This page lists video topics (tags). Click any tag to view related videos.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/topics/","section":"Topics","summary":"","title":"Topics","type":"topics"},{"content":"A growing collection of working configs and reference templates I use across my homelab and projects. Organized by topic — grab the folder you need and adapt it.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/resources/tutorials/","section":"Resources","summary":"","title":"tutorials","type":"repo"},{"content":"Welcome — this page is an index of my YouTube videos. Click any video to open its page or use the Topics page to filter by tag.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/videos/","section":"Videos","summary":"","title":"Videos","type":"videos"},{"content":"Hi! 👋 I\u0026rsquo;m Tars. Welcome to my cycling and tech education site — where I share insights, videos, and training ideas to help you be Tech Nerd like me.\n","date":"4 November 2025","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/","section":"Welcome to ElikesBikes","summary":"","title":"Welcome to ElikesBikes","type":"page"},{"content":"","date":"31 August 2024","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/videos/august-31-2024/","section":"Videos","summary":"","title":"August 31, 2024","type":"videos"},{"content":"","date":"31 August 2024","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/tags/cycling/","section":"Tags","summary":"","title":"Cycling","type":"tags"},{"content":"","date":"31 August 2024","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/tags/","section":"Tags","summary":"","title":"Tags","type":"tags"},{"content":"","date":"18 June 2024","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/videos/2024-giro-di-san-diego-california/","section":"Videos","summary":"","title":"2024 - Giro di San Diego - California","type":"videos"},{"content":"","date":"18 June 2024","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/tags/california/","section":"Tags","summa